Class LuaTable

java.lang.Object
com.spag.lua.LuaTable
All Implemented Interfaces:
LuaObject
public class LuaTable extends Object implements LuaObject
Class to represent lua tables and decoded them from a serialized lua table string (as per the Minecraft OpenComputers mod serialization library), some specifics may not yet be implimented

NOTE: indexed values index from 1 to preserve behaviour from lua for pairs, ipairs and because tables may be speciallly formulated to account for this

Author:
MR_Spagetty

    • merge

      public LuaTable merge(LuaTable b)
      merges anouther luaTable into this one

      indexed items from the other table will be added after items from this one

      keyed items from the other table will overide corresponding items in this one

      Parameters:
      b - the table to merge from
      Returns:
      this table after the merge operation to allow multiple consecutive opperations in a single statement

    • fromString

      public static LuaTable fromString(String data)
      parses a LuaTable that is serialized into a string

      deserializes the table from the Minecraft OpenComputers mod's serialization format into a representation of the oringonal LuaTable using the classes from this Library

      Parameters:
      data - the serialized string representation of the table
      Returns:
      the parsed table
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the table is invalid
      Implimentation Note:
      may not currently allow all possible serialized data
